Write a **Project Milestones** section for this proposal.

The total project timeline is {{ timeline }}. Budget is {{ budget }}.

Generate 4–6 clearly defined milestones that span the full project lifecycle. For each milestone include:

- **Milestone name** (action-oriented, e.g. "Discovery & Architecture Complete")
- **Duration** (e.g. "Weeks 1–2")
- **Key activities** (3–5 bullet points of concrete work items)
- **Deliverable(s)** (what the client receives at the end of this milestone)
- **Client dependencies** (what you need FROM the client to start or complete this milestone)

Milestones should follow a logical progression:
1. Discovery / Requirements (always first)
2. Design / Architecture
3. Core Development phase(s)
4. Testing & QA
5. Launch / Deployment
6. Handover & Support (if timeline allows)

Calibrate milestone duration to the overall timeline. A 3-month project has shorter milestones than a 12-month one.

Format each milestone as a ### sub-header followed by a structured list. Do not use a table — use formatted lists only.
